'''Igor Matanović''' (born 31 March 2003) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for {{German football updater|SCFreibu}} club [[SC Freiburg]].<ref name="WF">{{WorldFootball.net}}</ref> Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==
Matanović played for the youth team of [[Harburger TB]] until 2010, when he moved to [[FC St. Pauli]]'s youth academy.<ref name="mopo">{{cite news |last=Rosenfeld |first=Buttje |url=https://www.mopo.de/sport/fc-st-pauli/-junge-ist-aussergewoehnlich--hat-der-fc-st--pauli-da-ein-neues-wunderkind--37617156 |title=Igor Matanovic: Der FC St. Pauli hat ein Supertalent im Sturm |trans-title=Igor Matanović: FC St. Pauli has a super talent up front |work=[[Hamburger Morgenpost]] |date=14 November 2020 |access-date=27 November 2020 |language=de}}</ref> He made his professional debut for St. Pauli's senior team in the [[2. Bundesliga]] on 27 November 2020, coming on as a substitute in the 87th minute for [[Rico Benatelli]] against [[VfL Osnabrück]]. The home match finished as a 1–0 loss.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma9114828/lineup/ |title=Germany » 2. Bundesliga 2020/2021 » 9. Round » FC St. Pauli – VfL Osnabrück 0:1 |work=WorldFootball.net |date=27 November 2020 |access-date=27 November 2020}}</ref>

On 30 August 2021, he signed a five-year contract for [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]; on the same day he returned to [[FC St. Pauli]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://profis.eintracht.de/news/eintracht-frankfurt-verpflichtet-igor-matanovic-135201|title=Eintracht verpflichtet Igor Matanovic|trans-title=Eintracht sign Matanović|publisher=[[Eintracht Frankfurt]] |date=30 August 2021 |access-date=31 August 2021|language=de}}</ref>

On 17 August 2023, Matanović moved to [[Karlsruher SC]] in [[2. Bundesliga]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Karlsruher SC|url=https://www.ksc.de/profis/saison/news/show/article/per-leihe-igor-matanovic-wechselt-in-den-ksc-sturm/|title=PER LEIHE: IGOR MATANOVIĆ WECHSELT IN DEN KSC-STURM|trans-title=ON LOAN: IGOR MATANOVIĆ JOINS THE KSC ATTACK|date=17 August 2023|access-date=18 August 2023|language=de}}</ref>

On 9 July 2025, Matanović joined [[SC Freiburg]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=SC Freiburg|url=https://www.scfreiburg.com/en/latest/news/first-team/2025-26/igor-matanovic-joins-sc-freiburg/|title=Igor Matanovic joins SC Freiburg|date=9 July 2025|access-date=12 July 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
In April 2022, he declared his intention to represent Croatia internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.total-croatia-news.com/sport/62394-igor-matanovic|title=19-Year-Old Igor Matanović Chooses Croatia National Team Over Germany|publisher=total croatia news|date=28 April 2012|access-date=8 May 2022|language=en|archive-date=5 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220705191557/https://www.total-croatia-news.com/sport/62394-igor-matanovic|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Matanović was called up to the senior [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]] for the first time for the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A|Nations League]] games against Portugal and Poland in September 2024.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dalić objavio popis igrača za početak Lige nacija|url=https://hns.team/vijesti/28191/dalic-objavio-popis-igraca-za-pocetak-lige-nacija/|access-date=4 September 2024|publisher=Croatian Football Federation|date=19 August 2024|language=hr}}</ref> He debuted on 5 September 2024 against Portugal at [[Estádio da Luz]]. He substituted [[Martin Baturina]] in the 61st minute, Portugal won 2–1.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698888/croatia-portugal|title=Portugal v Croatia game report|date=5 September 2024}}</ref>

